                     <p> Indenture witnessing that <persName>
                           <forename>Richard</forename>, the abbot</persName>, and <orgName key="org_102002">convent of Begham</orgName> demise to <persName>
                           <forename>John</forename>
                           <surname>Awod</surname>
                        </persName> and <persName>
                           <forename>Joan</forename> his wife, of the parish of
                  <placeName role="person" key="place_102084">Jenyngton</placeName>
                        </persName>, a piece of land in <placeName key="place_102117">Otham</placeName> in co. Sussex, called <placeName type="minor">Grete Otham</placeName>, for 40 years, at an annual rent of 10s. 
                  Dated at <placeName role="date" key="place_102027">Beigham</placeName>, <origDate notBefore="1503-08-22" notAfter="1504-08-21">20 October, 19 Hen. VII</origDate>. 
